    "Header": "Cancer is complicated. For the world's highest impact, hardest-to-treat illnesses like pancreatic cancer, developing novel therapies requires looking beyond single-pathway genetic or biochemical analyses and getting a view of the entire picture. Multiplexed imaging and spatial proteomics with Cell DIVE from Leica Microsystems is a way to achieve highly multiplexed images (with 60+ biomarkers) in a single piece of human tissue using a robust, tissue-preserving workflow.\nIn this story, we will introduce you to the complex biology of pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma (PDAC) and investigate molecular and spatial determinants of tumor cell agression at the level of metabolism, apoptosis, and immunity.",
